text: The problem with Diary of a Wimpy Kid as a movie series is that the books span over 3 months or so and a movie takes a few years to complete. Harry Potter worked because the actors started young and it was believable because they were going through one school year per movie. The time cycle of the films was logical and it could work using the same actors. In the other movies, Greg hit puberty and was a foot taller by the 3rd installment. This series just doesn't work with the same young actors. I don't know why they replaced the adults because it should be possible to keep them the same. Overall, trying to restart this isn't a good idea, and the like to dislike ratio proves that already.
